🖥️ Linux Portfolio Desktop — Project Overview
🌍 Concept

Linux Portfolio Desktop is a web-based interactive simulation of a Linux desktop environment (GNOME-style), inspired by Kali Linux and Debian-based systems.

Instead of a traditional portfolio website, the entire user experience is transformed into a realistic desktop operating system inside the browser. Users interact with the interface as if they were using a real computer.

The goal is to present a personal profile in a fun, immersive, and highly interactive way, where exploring the desktop reveals information about the developer (not heavy projects, but personal profile content such as CV, skills, and identity).

🎯 Main Idea

The user enters a website.

They are welcomed by a Linux GNOME/Kali-style desktop environment.

They can interact with the system like a real OS:

Open folders

Open a CV (PDF viewer)

Use a terminal

Browse profile information

Everything is simulated but feels like a real operating system.

👉 It is basically:
“My PC desktop, but inside a browser as my portfolio.”

🧠 Key Philosophy

Minimal traditional website pages

Maximum interaction and immersion

Portfolio = Operating System experience

Focus on UI/UX realism, not heavy backend logic

Lightweight but visually powerful

