⚙️ Technical Architecture
🧱 Frontend (Core)

Next.js (React) → application framework

TypeScript → type safety and scalability

🎨 UI / Design Layer

Tailwind CSS → fast styling

shadcn/ui → modern UI components

Lucide / Phosphor icons → clean system icons

🧠 State Management (Desktop Engine)

Zustand → manage:

open windows

active apps

desktop state

🪟 Window System

react-rnd or dnd-kit:

drag windows

resize windows

handle layering (z-index)

💻 Terminal System

xterm.js

custom command parser:

maps commands → profile data responses


✨ Animations

Framer Motion → UI transitions (open/close windows)

GSAP (optional) → boot screen / advanced effects


🎨 UX / Design Goals

Must feel like a real Linux desktop

Smooth animations (no lag)

Real OS interaction feeling

Clean GNOME/Kali aesthetic

Dark mode default (hacker vibe)

Highly immersive experience


🎯 Purpose

Creative portfolio presentation

Showcase frontend + UI/UX skills

Demonstrate ability to build complex interactive interfaces

Stand out from traditional portfolio websites

Provide memorable “desktop experience” for visitors


🔥 Final Vision

When someone opens the site:

They don’t see a website…
They see a real Linux desktop
and they explore a developer’s identity like they are using his personal computer.

🧠 Summary (1 sentence)

A fully interactive Linux GNOME-style desktop simulation in the browser that transforms a developer portfolio into an immersive operating system experience.


